        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 2:17PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 216 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over George Washington
Carver St Pk, or 8 miles east of Cartersville, moving northeast at 25
mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, up to penny sized hail and frequent
cloud to ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Canton, Cartersville, Woodstock, Holly Springs, Emerson, Waleska,
Buffington, Hickory Flat, Union Hill, Lake Arrowhead, Kellogg Creek,
Red Top Mountain State Park, Little River Landing, George Washington
Carver St Pk, Lebanon, Sutallee, Hobgood Park, Bridgemill, and Oak
Grove.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
